IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: TO MATCH RESIDENCY AND FELLOWSHIP APPLICANTS WITH TRAINING PROGRAMS OF THEIR CHOICE.
IRS990.MissionDesc: TO MATCH HEALTHCARE PROFESSIONALS TO GRADUATE MEDICAL EDUCATION AND ADVANCED TRAINING PROGRAMS THROUGH A PROCESS THAT IS FAIR, EFFICIENT, TRANSPARENT, AND RELIABLE. TO PROVIDE MEANINGFUL AND ACCESSIBLE MATCH DATA AND ANALYSIS TO STAKEHOLDERS.
IRS990.Desc: HEALTH PROFESSIONS MATCHING PROGRAM - ORGANIZE AND CONDUCT A NATIONAL CLEARING HOUSE TO MATCH PHYSICIANS AND OTHER HEALTH PROFESSIONS APPLICANTS WITH GRADUATE EDUCATION PROGRAMS OF THEIR CHOICE. FOR FISCAL YEAR 2017, THERE WERE 39,275 RESIDENCY AND FELLOWSHIP PHYSICIAN APPLICANTS MATCHED.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 1
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE SHALL NUMBER EIGHT AND SHALL INCLUDE THE CHAIR, THE CHAIR ELECT, THE IMMEDIATE PAST CHAIR, THE SECRETARY/TREASURER, ONE STUDENT DIRECTOR, AND ONE RESIDENT PHYSICIAN DIRECTOR. THE OFFICERS AND THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE SHALL BE ELECTED BY THE BOARD AT ITS ANNUAL MEETING. BETWEEN MEETINGS OF THE BOARD, THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE SHALL HAVE AND EXERCISE ALL OF THE AUTHORITY OF THE BOARD IN THE MANAGEMENT OF CORPORATION, EXCEPT TO THE EXTENT, IF ANY, THAT SUCH AUTHORITY SHALL BE LIMITED BY RESOLUTION OF THE BOARD. THE DELEGATION OF AUTHORITY TO THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE SHALL NOT RELIEVE THE DIRECTORS OF ANY RESPONSIBILITY IMPOSED UPON THEM BY LAW. THE FINANCE AND AUDIT COMMITTEE SHALL BE CHAIRED BY THE SECRETARY/TREASURER OF THE ORGANIZATION AND INCLUDE OTHER BOARD MEMBERS ELECTED BY THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS. THE FINANCE AND AUDIT COMMITTEE SHALL HAVE RESPONSIBILITY FOR OVERSIGHT OF THE ORGANIZATION'S FINANCIAL REPORTING AND INVESTMENT PROCEDURES, THE ANNUAL AUDIT OF THE ORGANIZATION'S FINANCES, MONITORING LIABILITY AND OTHER INSURANCE COVERAGE FOR THE ORGANIZATION AND ITS DIRECTORS AND OFFICERS, AND ENSURING COMPLIANCE WITH APPLICABLE FEDERAL, STATE, AND LOCAL LAWS AND REGULATIONS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 4
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE CHANGES OT THE BYLAWS INCLUDED THE FOLLOWING: THREE NOMINATING ORGANIZATIONS WERE REMOVED FROM THE BYLAWS AND THE TERM OF THE IMMEDIATE PAST CHAIR WAS EXTEDED FROM ONE YEAR TO TWO YEARS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: A DRAFT OF THE FORM 990 WILL BE PROVIDED TO EACH MEMBER OF THE BOARD FOR REVIEW AND TO REQUEST CHANGES PRIOR TO FILING.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: EACH DIRECTOR, PRINCIPAL OFFICER AND MEMBER OF A COMMITTEE WITH GOVERNING BOARD DELEGATED POWERS SHALL ANNUALLY SIGN A STATEMENT WHICH AFFIRMS SUCH PERSON: A) HAS RECEIVED A COPY OF THE CONFLICTS OF INTEREST POLICY; B) HAS READ AND UNDERSTANDS THE POLICY; C) HAS AGREED TO COMPLY WITH THE POLICY; AND D) UNDERSTANDS NATIONAL RESIDENT MATCHING PROGRAM IS CHARITABLE AND IN ORDER TO MAINTAIN ITS FEDERAL TAX EXEMPTION IT MUST ENGAGE PRIMARILY IN ACTIVITIES WHICH ACCOMPLISH ONE OR MORE OF ITS TAX-EXEMPT PURPOSES.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE PRESIDENT'S SALARY, SALARY INCREASES, BENEFITS AND/OR BONUSES SHALL BE SET FORTH BY A COMPENSATION COMMITTEE COMPRISED OF THE CHAIR, CHAIR ELECT, AND PAST CHAIR OF THE BOARD OF THE NATIONAL RESIDENT MATCHING PROGRAM. A MARKET PRICING ANALYSIS WAS PERFORMED BY NONPROFIT HR TO DETERMINE RECOMMENDED SALARY RANGES AND MERIT MATRIX STRUCTURES. NONPROFIT HR REVIEWS MOVEMENT OF SALARY RANGES FOR SIMILAR POSITIONS IN THE DC MARKET, AS WELL AS THE AVERAGE SALARY INCREASES FOR EMPLOYEES IN THE NONPROFIT SECTOR. THE SENIOR TEAM AND CEO POSITIONS WERE INCLUDED IN THIS REVIEW.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION DOES NOT MAKE ITS GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY, AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AVAILABLE TO THE PUBLIC.
